# TypeScript build (lib)

**After editing any `.ts` file in `lib/` that has a co-located `.js` (e.g. `lib/page/*.ts`), run the compile command below** so the browser loads the updated code. Do not forget to recompile.

When compiling a single TS file in `lib/` (e.g. `lib/page/game_of_life_cpp.ts`), **do not use `--outDir`**. Emit the `.js` in the same folder as the `.ts`:

From project root:
```bash
cd lib && npx tsc page/game_of_life_cpp.ts --esModuleInterop --target es2019 --module esnext --skipLibCheck --strict
```

Or from `lib/`:
```bash
npx tsc page/game_of_life_cpp.ts --esModuleInterop --target es2019 --module esnext --skipLibCheck --strict
```

Output: `lib/page/game_of_life_cpp.js` (same folder as the source).

Using `--outDir page` can place the .js in a subfolder; omit it so output stays alongside the .ts.
